page.title: 08MINTSFEET TRADING ESTATE
page.content: { Mintsfeet}is so named as it is at the foot of the river{Mint,}a tribut- ary of the{Kent.}Not so long ago, Mintsfeet was a marshy flood plain. The land was sold very cheaply to a group of men who put marl into the marshland. Now a lot of the earlier buildings such as ATS Tyre Services have cracks in their walls caused by subsidence and substandard foundations Newer buildings are built on much deeper foundations that are able to hold the weight of the new buildings. The main part of Kendal's industrial wholesalers reside on the trading estate. These{include}mainly motor showrooms, foodstores, garages,The Milk Marketing Board & Farley Health.
